Not only have the logo on the website but what about putting in custom
JavaDoc tags which point at the JUnit test methods.

	-----Original Message-----
	From: Mike Clark [mailto:mike@...] 
	Sent: Monday, February 24, 2003 8:27 PM
	To: junit@yahoogroups.com
	Subject: Re: [junit] Re: What's the deal with the frog?
	
	
	Scott Stirling wrote:
	
	>Maybe we should have a contest to come up with a better frog,
or have a vote
	>to do away with the frog and come up with a cool logo for
JUnit, like they
	>do for a lot of the Jakarta projects.
	>
	
	I've often thought a "Tested with JUnit" graphic would be cool.
If you 
	saw it on a project's web page, for example, then you'd assume
there 
	were JUnit tests you could run.  Perhaps that graphic could be a

	recognizable variation of the standard logo.
